# .trivyignore — Trivy vulnerability suppression file
#
# This file documents intentional suppressions for vulnerabilities that cannot
# be remediated without a breaking major-version upgrade.  Each entry is
# accompanied by a justification and a re-evaluation date.
#
# Process: re-evaluate every suppression when the project upgrades Next.js to
# a major version that resolves the underlying issue (currently next@15+).

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2026-41305  (GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93)
# PostCSS < 8.5.10 — XSS via unescaped </style> in CSS Stringify Output
#
# Root cause: next@14.2.35 (the latest 14.x release) bundles postcss@8.4.31
# as a private dependency inside node_modules/next/node_modules/postcss.  npm
# overrides cannot reach bundled deps; the fix is only available in next@15+.
#
# Impact assessment: the vulnerability requires an attacker to control CSS
# that is processed by PostCSS stringify at build time — not a runtime attack
# surface for this project.  No end-user data passes through PostCSS stringify
# in production.
#
# Re-evaluate: when upgrading to next@15.x
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CVE-2026-41305

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CVE-2025-59471  (GHSA-9g9p-9gw9-jx7f)
# Next.js < 15.5.10 — DoS via Image Optimizer remotePatterns configuration
#
# Root cause: advisory range covers all 14.x versions.  next@14.2.35 is the
# final patch release for the 14.x line; Vercel does not backport this fix.
#
# Impact assessment: this project does not configure remotePatterns in
# next.config.mjs and does not expose the /_next/image endpoint to untrusted
# external image URLs.  The attack surface is therefore not present.
#
# Re-evaluate: when upgrading to next@15.x
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
CVE-2025-59471
# .trivyignore — Trivy CVE suppression list for Open-Audit
#
# Format: one CVE ID per line, optionally followed by a comment.
# Only suppress CVEs that have been reviewed and confirmed to be either:
#   (a) not reachable via the code paths in this project, or
#   (b) fixed upstream but the fix has not yet propagated to a release.
#
# ── Node.js / npm ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# None currently suppressed.
#
# ── Rust / Cargo ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# None currently suppressed.
#
# Add entries below as needed, e.g.:
# CVE-2024-XXXXX  # crate: foo, not reachable — we never call foo::bar()
